	<file-name>640ad5ba-a3e0-ea33-7f83-c69af5bef12f.xml</file-name>
	<internal-name>Callout left two</internal-name>
	<call_out_content_html>&lt;h2 class="title--md no-margin-top" style="color: var(--color-text-heading); margin-bottom: 0px; line-height: var(--heading-line-height); font-weight: 500; font-size: 32px; margin-top: 0px; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-style: italic; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;On the topic of providing for your kids when you pass away, having a properly written Will is absolutely essential for this. A Will is a legal document that explains what should happen to your assets when you pass away. If your goal is to create generational wealth, then your Will is the tool that is going to make that happen.&lt;/h2&gt;</call_out_content_html>
