<component id="12145ed3-ff60-2d98-f6d0-649d7f3df0c6">
	<content-type>/component/component-articlesection</content-type>
	<display-template>/templates/web/components/article-section.ftl</display-template>
	<no-template-required/>
	<merge-strategy>inherit-levels</merge-strategy>
	<objectGroupId>1214</objectGroupId>
	<objectId>12145ed3-ff60-2d98-f6d0-649d7f3df0c6</objectId>
	<internal-name>Sec 4</internal-name>
	<sectionClass_s>no-margin-bottom</sectionClass_s>
	<file-name>12145ed3-ff60-2d98-f6d0-649d7f3df0c6.xml</file-name>
	<sectionContent_html>&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;The reason that a Will is so important is that if you die and you haven&amp;rsquo;t left a Will, then your assets will be distributed according to legislation governing estates. In simple terms, that means that the government will decide who gets what, and it might not be the people whom you wanted, or in the way you wanted it. So for that reason, you really need to ensure that you have a legally sound Will in place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;But also, a Will should limit disputes amongst your family about who should get what. Your death will naturally be upsetting for your family, so the last thing we want is to create more drama for them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;We suggest that you get your Will drafted asap because it&amp;rsquo;s just so important. Please don&amp;rsquo;t leave it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class="text--md" style="color: var(--color-text-heading); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); line-height: var(--heading-line-height); font-weight: 500; font-size: var(--text-md); font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;3. Discuss it with your kids&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;If you&amp;rsquo;re serious about creating generational wealth, then the best thing you can do is to involve your adult kids in all discussions around estate planning and how to manage your assets and belongings after you pass away.&lt;/p&gt;</sectionContent_html>
